&gt; I think the ExtractorJS code is assuming that a &#39;via&#39; URI will be
&gt; available to serve as the implied base HREF. This is usually
&gt; the case for Javascript content, but should not be assumed.
&gt; 
&gt; I don&#39;t think any recent (just before 1.6) changes would have made
&gt; this error more common; is there any chance you&#39;ve recently started
&gt; using a larger seed list or manually feeding more URIs into a running
&gt; crawl (such that URIs returning Javascript would lack &#39;via&#39; URIs)?
&gt; 
&gt; In any case, it&#39;s a bug -- if no &#39;via&#39; is available the URI from
&gt; which the Javascript itself was returned is probably the next
&gt; best &#39;base&#39; to use for derelativizing relative URIs.
&gt; 
&gt; - Gordon @ IA
